President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. Brigadier General Allison A. Hickey is nominated for Under Secretary for Benefits at the Department of Veterans Affairs. Jenni R. LeCompte is nominated for Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs at the Department of the Treasury. Steve Muro is nominated for Under Secretary for Memorial Affairs at the Department of Veterans Affairs. Virginia A. Seitz is nominated for Assistant Attorney General, Office of Legal Counsel at the Department of Justice. Lafe E. Solomon is nominated for General Counsel at the National Labor Relations Board. Each of these individuals brings extensive experience and expertise to their respective roles.